207 to 225 Varick Street, west side, from Houston (formerly Hammersley Street) to Clarkson Streets. All of these old houses, except Nos. 223, 225, the two at the Clarkson Street end of the block, are frame buildings faced with brick. They are shortly to be demolished to make room for the Maltz Building.
June, 1925.

A general view of the "Greenwich Village" section as photo- northward from a point in the air over Varick Street (lower center). The commercial structures there flank both sides of this thorough- fare below West Houston Street. Varick Street changes its identity above the bend to become Seventh Avenue. At the right is Sixth Avenue's extension under construction. Note the old "El" line on same above W. 3rd Street. The clearly defined thoroughfare at the left is Hudson Street. Eighth Avenue branches off of the latter in the upper left corner. Tortuous Greenwich Street and its nearly parallel Washington Street are closer to the left margin.

Ewing Galloway
